From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenBook Build <build@openbook.invalid>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 0001/0001] branding: add openbook browser brand directory

Introduces browser/branding/openbook/ with brand strings and build
integration. Selected via --with-branding=browser/branding/openbook in
all per-platform mozconfigs.

The repository's branding/openbook/ directory is the single source of truth:
build/scripts/build.sh stages it over this directory before the build, so the
files created here are deliberately IDENTICAL to the repo copies (the staging
copy is then a no-op for them). The patch exists so the brand directory is
complete even before staging and so `mach` configure/jar processing finds the
moz.build/jar.mn it expects.

KNOWN GAP (release blocker, tracked in branding/README.md and
docs/RELEASE-CHECKLIST.md): platform raster icons (firefox.ico, firefox.icns,
default*.png — upstream file names, OpenBook art) are generated from the SVG
sources per branding/openbook/content/branding.json; the generator must run
before the Phase 1 release gate. jar.mn below references ONLY assets that
exist today (SVGs), so a build does not fail on missing rasters.
